SUMMARY:Deadline: MIT R&D Collaboration Projects 2026 (MKB Innovatiestimule
 ring Topsectoren)
DESCRIPTION:The MIT R&D Collaboration Projects scheme (MIT R&D-samenwerking
 sprojecten\, part of MKB Innovatiestimulering Topsectoren) funds joint R&D
  projects by Dutch SMEs within the national Top Sectors and Mission-driven
  Innovation policy. The grant covers 35 percent of eligible costs: small p
 rojects of EUR 50\,000-200\,000 and large projects of EUR 200\,000-350\,00
 0 (with per-participant ranges of EUR 25\,000-100\,000 for small and EUR 2
 5\,000-175\,000 for large). Eligible applicants are consortia of at least 
 two collaborating SMEs\, with no single participant carrying more than 70 
 percent of costs. The national RVO round runs 9 June to 15 September 2026 
 (closes 17:00) and is a ranked tender\, not first-come-first-served\; some
  provinces run separate regional MIT windows. No application fee. Apply vi
 a RVO.\n\nOrganisation: Rijksdienst voor Ondernemend Nederland (RVO)\nLoca
 tion: Netherlands. SME consortia (minimum two collaborating SMEs).\nAward:
  Grant covering 35 percent of eligible costs. Small projects EUR 50\,000-2
 00\,000\; large projects EUR 200\,000-350\,000 per project (EUR 25\,000-10
 0\,000 or EUR 25\,000-175\,000 per participant). No application fee.\nDura
 tion: Project-based\; ranked tender (not first-come).\n\nMore: https://www
 .rvo.nl/subsidies-financiering/mit/rd-samenwerkingsprojecten
URL:https://www.rvo.nl/subsidies-financiering/mit/rd-samenwerkingsprojecten
LOCATION:Netherlands. SME consortia (minimum two collaborating SMEs).
END:VEVENT
